This paper discusses the use of thermal imaging to track physiological and affective cues in humans, which falls under the categories of computer vision (cs.CV) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The paper also mentions the use of machine learning techniques to analyze the thermal images, which could fall under the categories of multimedia (cs.MM), machine learning (cs.LG), and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE).
